Headaches are a symptom of preeclampsia. Other signs and symptoms are pitting adema in the ankles, hands, or face, (if you press a finger into the swollen tissue and the imprint doesnt pop right back out, that is pitting adema) dizziness, blurred vision,floaters in the vision, upper abdominal pain, confusion and you can be checked for high blood pressure, and protein in the urine.
